@coffeekraken.s-docblock.shared.SDockblo.name: SDockblock

source.name: source
source.description: The docblock source. Can be either a string to parse or a filePath

settings.name: settings
settings.description: An object of settings to configure the SDocblock instance:
settings.content: - tags ({}) {Object}: An object representing the functions used to parse each tags. The object format is ```{ tagName: parseFn }```

@coffeekraken.s-docblock.shared.SDockblo.description:
This is the main class that expose the methods like "parse", etc...
You have to instanciate it by passing a settings object. Here's the available options:

sort.name: sort

sortFunction.name: sortFunction
sortFunction.description: Specify a custom sort function you want to use. If not set, use the ```sortFunction``` setting.

sort.description:
This method allows you to set the order in which you want to get the
blocks back when using the methods like get blocks, etc...

parse.name: parse
parse.description:
This method is the principal one. Use it to parse a string
and get back the object version of it

toobject.name: toObject
toobject.description: This method convert the parsed docblocks to a simple object

tostring.name: toString
tostring.description: This method allows you to get the string version of the docblock(s)

@coffeekraken.s-docblock.shared.SDocbloc.name: SDocblockBlock

settings.name: settings
settings.description: A settings object to configure your instance

@coffeekraken.s-docblock.shared.SDocbloc.description:
This class represent a docblock object that contains all the "tags" values and some features like:
- Converting the block to markdown
- More to come...

tagsmap.name: tagsMap
tagsmap.description: Store the default tags mapping to their parsing functions

registertag.name: registerTag

tagName.name: tagName
tagName.description: The tag you want to register without the @

parser.name: parser
parser.description: A function that will be called with the string tag content. You can parse this string and return an object that represent the tag data

registertag.description:
This static method allows you to register a new tag that will
be recognized by the SDocblockBlock class.

tostring.name: toString
tostring.description: This method return the passed source string

toobject.name: toObject
toobject.description: This method return the parsed docblock object

@coffeekraken.s-docblock.node.utils.firs.name: firstDocblockWithNamespaceInFolder

directory.name: directory
directory.description: The directory in which to search for files with the namespace tag

settings.name: settings
settings.description: A settings object to configure your navigation generation:
settings.content: - exclude ('*\/+(__tests__ | __wip__)\') {String}: Specify a glob pattern representing the files to exclude from the generation

@coffeekraken.s-docblock.node.utils.firs.description:
This function search in the passed folder for files containing a "@namespace" tag (and an "@name" optional one)
and generate a SNav instance with all these founded files as sources...

@coffeekraken.s-docblock.shared.interfac.name: SDocblockSettingsInterface
@coffeekraken.s-docblock.shared.interfac.description: This class represent the interface that describe SDocblock settings

filePath.description: Specify the file path of the parsed file

filter.description: Specify a filter function that will be called on each docblock. If return false, the docblock will be ignored

filterByTag.description: Specify a filter function by tag. This mean that this object must have as property the tagname you want to filter by, and a filter function as value

renderMarkdown.description: Specify if you want to render the markdown inside the tag contents or not

markedOptions.description: Specify some options for the marked library
